# Vodacom Caller Tunes (BizTune) — Project Overview

Business caller-tune subscription platform: customers pay via Selcom USSD push,
ops manually produce the audio "beat" and install it on Vodacom.

## Architecture

- **Backend:** Laravel 10 API (repo root). Entry: `routes/api.php`, `routes/tunes.php`,
  `routes/callbacks.php`, `routes/management.php`.
- **Frontends:** 4 CRA React portals under `portals/`:
  - `customer/` — public subscription form (no login)
  - `admin-portal/` — admin panel
  - `vodacom-agents-portal/` — agents
  - `referrals-agents-portal/` — referrals/commission portal
- **Payments:** Selcom (`app/Adapters/Selcom/`). Config in `config/selcom.php`.
- **Core domain:** `app/Services/TunesSubscriptionService.php`,
  models `TuneSubscription`, `TuneSubscriptionPhone`, `TuneSubscriptionPackage`,
  `SelcomTransaction`, `Customer`, `ReferralAgent`.

## Environments

- **Local:** `php artisan serve` on 127.0.0.1:8000; portals via `yarn start`.
- **Production VPS:** DigitalOcean `165.22.124.111` (2GB RAM), Docker Compose
  (`docker-compose.prod.fast.yml`): `vodacom-mysql`, `vodacom-api`, `vodacom-web` (nginx).
- **IMPORTANT:** In production Laravel reads `.env.production` (because APP_ENV=production
  makes Laravel prefer `.env.production` over `.env`). New env vars MUST be added there.
- Subdomains (Cloudflare → VPS): admin.biztune.co.tz, agent.biztune.co.tz,
  referrals.biztune.co.tz. Customer portal: https://165.22.124.111 (port 443 default).

## Git

- Primary remote: `vodacombeat` → github.com/giseedeveloper/VodacomBEAT (branch `main`).
- Never commit `.env`, `.env.production`, or Selcom secrets.

## Known legacy issues (do not replicate)

- Two subscription systems coexist: legacy `subscriptions` table vs `tune_subscriptions`.
- `tune_subscriptions` has NO status column — state is inferred from nullable timestamps.
- Selcom webhook has no idempotency; commission can double-disburse on duplicate callbacks.
